.TH HYPRWINDOWS 1 "January 2026" "hyprwindows" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
hyprwindows \- Hyprland window rules manager
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hyprwindows
.RI [ options ]
.RI [ command ]
.RI [ args ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B hyprwindows
is a TUI and CLI tool for managing Hyprland window rules defined in JSON/JSONC format.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B (none)
Launch the interactive TUI.
.TP
.B \-\-tui
Explicitly launch the TUI.
.TP
.BI summarize " rules.json"
Display rules grouped by tag.
.TP
.BI scan-dotfiles " dotfiles_dir rules.json" " [appmap.json]"
Scan dotfiles directory and report apps missing window rules.
.TP
.BI active " rules.json"
Show active windows and which rules match them.
.TP
.B \-\-help
Show usage information.
.SH TUI CONTROLS
.TP
.B Up/Down
Navigate menu
.TP
.B Enter
Execute selected action
.TP
.B PgUp/PgDn
Scroll output
.TP
.B s
Open settings
.TP
.B q
Quit
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/hypr/windowrules.jsonc
Default rules file location (configurable in TUI settings).
.TP
.I data/appmap.json
Application to window class mapping.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Summarize rules:
.B hyprwindows summarize ~/.config/hypr/windowrules.jsonc
.TP
Find missing rules:
.B hyprwindows scan-dotfiles ~/dotfiles ~/.config/hypr/windowrules.jsonc
.TP
Check active windows:
.B hyprwindows active ~/.config/hypr/windowrules.jsonc
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR hyprctl (1),
.BR hyprland (1)
